  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0d9f\u0dba \u0d91\u0dc5\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel shortage lowers vegetable prices",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Traders and farmers who came to Dambulla Economic Center say that due to the shortage of fuel across the country, the price of vegetables has to come down greatly and because of fuel smuggling across the country, vegetable farmers as well as traders who buy vegetables have been put under pressure.",
        "They point out that the price of vegetables has fallen to some extent these days and the main reason is fuel shortage.",
        "On the afternoon of the 30th in the Dambulla Economic Center, it was possible to see large stocks of vegetables being kept in a way that could not be sold.",
        "Farmers claim that they have brought their produce to the market amid difficulties since morning but have not been able to sell it at a proper price due to the decrease in the number of traders coming from outside to buy vegetables.",
        "They also point out that some vendors who come to the economic center ask for their products at low prices.",
        "Traders coming to the economic center to buy vegetables said that they could not get fuel because of the smugglers even though they were standing in front of the filling stations to get fuel.",
        "Therefore, no matter how cheaply the vegetables are bought from outsiders at higher prices, consumers have to sell vegetables at higher prices because of the higher fuel purchase.",
        "They say that most of the traders have stopped trading vegetables completely, some businessmen said that ten to fifteen traders gathered in one truck and took a very limited amount of vegetables because of work.",
        "Due to this reason, farmers end up selling vegetables at a very low price, they point out.",
        "It is special that a kilo of lis which was sold at high prices between 180 and 200 rupees in Dambulla Economic Center has reduced to 60 to 70 rupees today.",
        "It is a unique thing that the economic center is able to see how the farmers are suffering from not being able to sell vegetables in the low country. The farmers claim that if fuel is given to the farmers and the traders who transport vegetables under a certain system, this kind of situation will not arise in the country."
      ],
